{"questionId":"9118608","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p><strong>Table 3</strong> shows the values of the consumer price index (CPI) between 2016 and 2020 in Kanyaland.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><strong>Table 3</strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><strong><img src=\"__IMG__/4fadd08aae5463d8d456b3720440005f61cd15c3.png\"></strong></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Using <strong>Table 3</strong>, calculate the rate of inflation in 2017 <strong>and</strong> in 2018.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>2017: <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>174</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>−</mo><mn>176</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>176</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow></mfrac></math> × 100 = −1.19 %</p>\n<p>2018: <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>172</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>9</mn><mo>−</mo><mn>174</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>174</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfrac></math> × 100 = −0.75 %</p>\n<p><em>Award <strong>[1]</strong> for each correct answer</em>.</p>\n<p><em>No workings are necessary. The % sign is not necessary</em>.</p>","meta":{"questionId":"9118608","referenceCode":"21N.3.HL.TZ0.2g","subjectId":"48-dp-economics","title":"Using Table 3, calculate the rate of inflation in 2017 and in 2018.","paper":"3","level":"HL","questionNumber":"g","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["First exams 2022","First exams 2022","Unit 3: Macroeconomics","3.3 Macroeconomic objectives","3.3.3 Low and stable rate of inflation","First exams 2022","Unit 3: Macroeconomics","3.3 Macroeconomic objectives","First exams 2022","Unit 3: Macroeconomics"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}